      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SLANEYSIDE WINX (1) is yet to miss the placings in an excellent record this trip which boasts two wins. Missed the frame latest (30.33) when fourth over 480m at this track in an A7. Looks suited and should go close. SEAVIEW CIAN (2) finished well back at this track last time when a 6 length sixth (30.50) but scored four back at this track (29.73). Can figure in the finish. HOLLYHILL PJ (5) got a clear run and led until the final stages when second and beaten half a length (29.83) at this track in an A6 over 480m. Has never been out of the placings from two starts out of this box. Overdue and expected to feature again. DAILY NEWS (3) was well supported last time but could only manage third (30.10), beaten 8 lengths. Well placed and gets his chance.",
